      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Prioritizing theoretical risks is not about ignoring present-day benefits, but about ensuring that the tools we use to solve diseases and climate change do not ultimately destroy the species that needs them. If AI develops unchecked, the existential threat could erase all future progress, meaning that theoretical safeguards are actually the foundation for any long-term medical or environmental breakthroughs. Responsible governance involves integrating safety protocols directly into the R&D process for beneficial applications rather than acting as a brake on innovation.",
